# Draft:Devitt Award

----
The Edward J. Devitt Distinguished Service to Justice Award is a prize given annually to a U.S. federal judge for distinguished and exceptional service.  The prize is named in honor of Edward J. Devitt, a U.S. district judge, and has been presented by the the Dwight D. Opperman Foundation since 1983. The award is intended to serve as a Nobel Prize for the federal judiciary.
